        "def standardise_scores(df: pd.DataFrame,\n",
        "                        score_cols: list = SCORE_COLS) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Z-score each assay column independently before averaging.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Why standardise before averaging?\n",
        "    ───────────────────────────────────\n",
        "    The six assays were run in different cell lines and with different\n",
        "    surface markers.  Their LFC distributions have different means and\n",
        "    standard deviations (e.g. CD33 assays reach LFC ≈ 3.3 while CD15\n",
        "    tops out at ≈ 1.6).  Averaging raw values would let high-range assays\n",
        "    dominate.  Z-scoring first puts every assay on a comparable scale so\n",
        "    that each contributes equally to the mean.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Standardisation is performed column-wise using the non-null values\n",
        "    in each column (μ and σ computed from the available scores only).\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    df         : pd.DataFrame\n",
        "    score_cols : list of str\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns\n",
        "    -------\n",
        "    pd.DataFrame — copy with score columns replaced by z-scored values\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    df = df.copy()\n",
        "    print(\"[standardise] Z-scoring each assay column:\")\n",
        "    for col in score_cols:\n",
        "        col_data  = df[col].dropna()\n",
        "        mu, sigma = col_data.mean(), col_data.std()\n",
        "        df[col]   = (df[col] - mu) / (sigma if sigma > 0 else 1.0)\n",
        "        n_valid   = col_data.shape[0]\n",
        "        print(f\"  {col:<18}  n={n_valid:>3}   μ={mu:.4f}   σ={sigma:.4f}\")\n",
        "    print()\n",
        "    return df"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rj1N3aTY6Anf"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def compute_mean_score(df: pd.DataFrame,\n",
        "                        score_cols: list = SCORE_COLS) -> pd.Series:\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Average the (standardised) assay scores across available columns\n",
        "    for each guide, ignoring NaN values (nanmean).\n",
        "\n",
        "    Each guide is measured in whichever assays are relevant to its target\n",
        "    antigen.  For example:\n",
        "        • A CD13-targeting guide has scores in NB4 CD13 and TF1 CD13 only.\n",
        "        • A CD33-targeting guide has scores in MOLM13 CD33, NB4 CD33,\n",
        "          TF1 CD33 (and possibly MOLM13 CD15 if it was cross-profiled).\n",
        "\n",
        "    Using nanmean means we exploit every available data point without\n",
        "    penalising guides that were not tested in irrelevant assays.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    df         : pd.DataFrame — dataframe with standardised score columns\n",
        "    score_cols : list of str\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns\n",
        "    -------\n",
