        "def rollup_position_shap(imp_df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Aggregate base-level SHAP importance back to position level.\n",
        "\n",
        "    For each position i (1–20), sum mean |SHAP| over all four bases\n",
        "    {A, T, G, C} to answer: \"How much does knowing the identity of\n",
        "    position i improve prediction, across all guides?\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    Also identifies the dominant base at each position — the nucleotide\n",
        "    whose presence has the strongest average absolute SHAP.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Biological interpretation\n",
        "    ─────────────────────────\n",
        "    Positions with high aggregated SHAP map to functionally important\n",
        "    regions of the guide:\n",
        "        • Seed/PAM-proximal (17–20): expected to rank highest\n",
        "        • Position 1 (G preference): U6 promoter effect\n",
        "        • Positions with homopolymer runs: structural disruption signal\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters\n",
        "    ----------\n",
        "    imp_df : pd.DataFrame — output of build_shap_importance_table()\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns\n",
        "    -------\n",
        "    pd.DataFrame — one row per position, sorted by total_shap descending\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    pos_df = imp_df[imp_df[\"feature_type\"] == \"positional\"].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    agg = (pos_df.groupby(\"position\")\n",
        "                 .agg(\n",
        "                     total_shap     = (\"mean_abs_shap\", \"sum\"),\n",
        "                     dominant_base  = (\"mean_abs_shap\",\n",
